<h2>2 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each block. Write what you think it does.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">def main_menu():
    print(&quot;1. 도감 보기&quot;)
    print(&quot;2. 종료&quot;)
    return input(&quot;선택: &quot;).strip()

choice = main_menu()
print(f&quot;고른 것: {choice}&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong><code>main_menu</code> both prints </strong>and<strong> returns. The user types <code>1</code>. What prints in total?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-python">while True:
    choice = input(&quot;선택: &quot;).strip()
    if choice == &quot;5&quot;:
        print(&quot;종료합니다&quot;)
        break
    else:
        print(&quot;계속&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>The user types <code>2</code>, then <code>5</code>. What happens each round?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-python">pokedex = [{&quot;name&quot;: &quot;피카츄&quot;}, {&quot;name&quot;: &quot;파이리&quot;}, {&quot;name&quot;: &quot;꼬부기&quot;}]
print(f&quot;{len(pokedex)}마리 등록&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What single line prints?</strong></p>
